{"text": " It's passion fruit season here in South Florida, so let's go pick some. My friend Zane over at Zane's World Nursery has one of these passion fruit vines that's absolutely enormous and covers this entire section. And there are so many fruits. Because passion fruit have a tough outer skin, you can wait until they drop off of the vine and then just go around and collect them all. It wasn't long before I had a whole little bag full of them. Back in the kitchen, I gave the passion fruit to quick wash, cut them in half, and then used a spoon to scoop out all the delicious seeds on the inside. And because we have so much passion fruit to work with, today I decided to make passion fruit curd. For anyone that's never tried this before, passion fruit curd can be used similar to the way you use jelly. You can just top it on toast and it's absolutely delicious. And it's super simple to make. All you want to do is add half a cup of your passion fruit, a pinch of salt, three quarters of a cup of white sugar, and three eggs to a bowl and give that a good mix. You want to make sure that the bowl you're using is heat resistant or just use a smaller pot because you want to add this to a larger pot with some simmering water to create a double boiler effect. And then just start for the next eight minutes until it starts to thicken. After it gets to a nice thicker consistency, I just like to remove it from the heat and then add one whole stick of butter, one little cube at a time, and mix it until it all melts and combines together. After it's all mixed together, it should look something like this. And then I just like to add it to jars so it can finish thickening and chill in the fridge. And just like that, you have homemade passion fruit curd that makes it delicious and easy breakfast in the morning. How it's time to see how it tastes. It's the perfect blend of sweet and sour and I'll definitely be enjoying this for breakfast this week. Passion fruit vines make a lot of fruit, so sometimes it can be difficult to use all of them, but this is definitely a 10 out of 10. So if you have a bunch of passion fruits, give this a try. And until next time, get outside and see what you can find.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 2.04, "text": " It's passion fruit season here in South Florida,", "tokens": [50364, 467, 311, 5418, 6773, 3196, 510, 294, 4242, 9117, 11, 50466], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10679938968292065, "compression_ratio": 1.782967032967033, "no_speech_prob": 0.00617549242451787}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 2.04, "end": 3.08, "text": " so let's go pick some.", "tokens": [50466, 370, 718, 311, 352, 1888, 512, 13, 50518], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10679938968292065, "compression_ratio": 1.782967032967033, "no_speech_prob": 0.00617549242451787}, {"id": 2, "seek": 0, "start": 3.08, "end": 5.32, "text": " My friend Zane over at Zane's World Nursery", "tokens": [50518, 1222, 1277, 1176, 1929, 670, 412, 1176, 1929, 311, 3937, 32992, 2109, 50630], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10679938968292065, "compression_ratio": 1.782967032967033, "no_speech_prob": 0.00617549242451787}, {"id": 3, "seek": 0, "start": 5.32, "end": 7.0, "text": " has one of these passion fruit vines", "tokens": [50630, 575, 472, 295, 613, 5418, 6773, 371, 1652, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10679938968292065, "compression_ratio": 1.782967032967033, "no_speech_prob": 0.00617549242451787}, {"id": 4, "seek": 0, "start": 7.0, "end": 10.32, "text": " that's absolutely enormous and covers this entire section.", "tokens": [50714, 300, 311, 3122, 11322, 293, 10538, 341, 2302, 3541, 13, 50880], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10679938968292065, "compression_ratio": 1.782967032967033, "no_speech_prob": 0.00617549242451787}, {"id": 5, "seek": 0, "start": 10.32, "end": 11.68, "text": " And there are so many fruits.", "tokens": [50880, 400, 456, 366, 370, 867, 12148, 13, 50948], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_lo